8 An Act relating to professions and occupations;
amending 59 O.S. 2021, Section 161.4, as amended by
9 Section 1, Chapter 1, O.S.L. 2024 (59 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 161.4), which relates to the Board of
10 Chiropractic Examiners; extending sunset date;
providing an effective date; and declaring an
11 emergency.
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 161.4, as
15 amended by Section 1, Chapter 1, O.S.L. 2024 (59 O.S. Supp. 2025,
16 Section 161.4), is amended to read as follows:
17 Section 161.4. A. A Board of Chiropractic Examiners is hereby
18 re-created to continue until July 1, 2026 2031, in accordance with
19 the provisions of the Oklahoma Sunset Law. The Board shall regulate
20 the practice of chiropractic in this state in accordance with the
21 provisions of the Oklahoma Chiropractic Practice Act. The Board,
22 appointed by the Governor, shall be composed of eight chiropractic
23 physicians and one lay member representing the public.
24 B. Each chiropractic physician member of the Board shall:
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3003 SFLR Page 1
